A==\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering JUnit Class Order**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking it might help to add JUnit properties to order my classes alphabetically. I noticed that the dynamic test class \\\\\\\"ComKenaiJffiInvoke...\\\\\\\" comes after \\\\\\\"ComKenaiJffiInitTest.\\\\\\\" It's tricky because \\\\\\\"Init\\\\\\\" starts with 'I' and \\\\\\\"Invoke\\\\\\\" starts with 'V', so I wonder if naming rules could help. Maybe I could configure the order with annotations like @Order. If the existing ones aren’t annotated, they could end up being treated as the lowest priority, which doesn’t feel right. Let’s see if I can make adjustments!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Planning for Dynamic Test Execution**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering the test execution order and if the existing tests are loaded first, especially with invalid properties, it could create issues. Should I make the dynamic tests run first? I’m thinking I might modify an existing test to handle a prior successful load gracefully. It seems like I’ll need to check for a library, but if it’s not loaded, I'll have to assert differently. I might want to rename the method while keeping the existing goal. Also, I should add a JUnit property to define the test class order properly—using “junit-platform.properties” should help!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Checking metadata generation**\\\\n\\\\nThe Java run for the test generates metadata, which is interesting! I need to check the user code filter; it might include \\\\\\\"com.kenai.\\\\\\\" I want to ensure it's set up correctly, so everything works as expected. I'm just making sure I'm covering all the bases — it’s important to check these details, as missing something could lead to unexpected issues down the line.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_as4wAgaaOQ9CuPYBFXEyFj5s|fc_0074da3690da544a0169f809142248819caf4918cf5f0c5c8e\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.github.jnr/jffi/1.3.9/user-code-filter.json\", \"limit\": 120}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 549, \"output\": 1330, \"cacheRead\": 27648, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 29527, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777862913317, \"responseId\": \"resp_0074da3690da544a0169f80901c6dc819c93666ecf9ac898cb\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.github.jnr:jffi:1.3.9/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-04T02-50-11-295800Z.log:2710:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_as4wAgaaOQ9CuPYBFXEyFj5s|fc_0074da3690da544a0169f809142248819caf4918cf5f0c5c8e\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\n  \\\"rules\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"excludeClasses\\\": \\\"**\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"includeClasses\\\": \\\"com.kenai.jffi.**\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777862932635}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.github.jnr:jffi:1.3.9/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-04T02-50-11-295800Z.log:2711:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_as4wAgaaOQ9CuPYBFXEyFj5s|fc_0074da3690da544a0169f809142248819caf4918cf5f0c5c8e\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\n  \\\"rules\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"excludeClasses\\\": \\\"**\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"includeClasses\\\": \\\"com.kenai.jffi.**\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777862932635}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.github.jnr:jffi:1.3.9/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-04T02-50-11-295800Z.log:2712:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering JUnit Class Order**\\n\\nI'm thinking it might help to add JUnit properties to order my classes alphabetically. I noticed that the dynamic test class \\\"ComKenaiJffiInvoke...\\\" comes after \\\"ComKenaiJffiInitTest.\\\" It's tricky because \\\"Init\\\" starts with 'I' and \\\"Invoke\\\" starts with 'V', so I wonder if naming rules could help. Maybe I could configure the order with annotations like @Order. If the existing ones aren’t annotated, they could end up being treated as the lowest priority, which doesn’t feel right. Let’s see if I can make adjustments!\\n\\n**Planning for Dynamic Test Execution**\\n\\nI’m considering the test execution order and if the existing tests are loaded first, especially with invalid properties, it could create issues. Should I make the dynamic tests run first? I’m thinking I might modify an existing test to handle a prior successful load gracefully. It seems like I’ll need to check for a library, but if it’s not loaded, I'll have to assert differently. I might want to rename the method while keeping the existing goal. Also, I should add a JUnit property to define the test class order properly—using “junit-platform.properties” should help!\\n\\n**Checking metadata generation**\\n\\nThe Java run for the test generates metadata, which is interesting! I need to check the user code filter; it might include \\\"com.kenai.\\\" I want to ensure it's set up correctly, so everything works as expected. I'm just making sure I'm covering all the bases — it’s important to check these details, as missing something could lead to unexpected issues down the line.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0074da3690da544a0169f809028608819c8eb7646cb3091897\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-AkUIfbo-0mF3tfpzFdESMSblSTpRgG15GshRLC-k9PmFGKtamHDaHibDm1ca7XYeMdD0o3brY7EyziIeenm4awlrkQjjzv6CurP5dHgHUb6fHi6-ZcC3wRYFpWvIfbMlazSfuoCL815ZZ0HVPF0RdnJAazuH5oaepgJwk12RL2z7CGyeAp42ckVMPK76makmmyGb4dOdd6Oc1E4qYIG