ight check `Library.getLastError()` if `defaultLibrary` is null, but maybe that’s not essential. Still, it could help avoid failures when the default library can’t open.\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.github.jnr:jffi:1.3.9/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-04T02-50-11-295800Z.log:3072:[thinking] I’m thinking through the properties of `Library.getDefault()` and whether it returns a cached default. It seems like the DefaultLibrary is initialized validly, which removes failure coverage but also avoids class order dependency. Still, if the native resources are invalid, it fails. What if in the init test, I check the property `Boolean.getBoolean(\"jffi.init.forceFailureTest\")` before overriding? Given class ordering, it may be fine in JUnit. Classes are likely discovered and ordered properly.\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.github.jnr:jffi:1.3.9/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-04T02-50-11-295800Z.log:3082:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating library defaults**\\n\\nI’m considering what happens if `Library.getDefault()` returns null. If `getDefault()` can return a valid instance but also possibly return null due to `openLibrary`, that creates a situation where asserting not null might not be necessary every time—especially if there's no error. I might check `Library.getLastError()` if `defaultLibrary` is null, but maybe that’s not essential. Still, it could help avoid failures when the default library can’t open.\\n\\n**Considering library initialization**\\n\\nI’m thinking through the properties of `Library.getDefault()` and whether it returns a cached default. It seems like the DefaultLibrary is initialized validly, which removes failure coverage but also avoids class order dependency. Still, if the native resources are invalid, it fails. What if in the init test, I check the property `Boolean.getBoolean(\\\"jffi.init.forceFailureTest\\\")` before overriding? Given class ordering, it may be fine in JUnit. Classes are likely discovered and ordered properly.\\n\\n**Considering Git Commands**\\n\\nI see I could add `@Order(2)` to the existing setup easily. It seems like showing differences, including untracked changes, might be unnecessary with `git diff -- /dev/null`. I want to keep things concise. However, mentioning untracked metadata from the status seems like a bad idea. Hmm, maybe I could also check the reachability of metadata using `git ls-files`? I'll weigh that option as I proceed.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0074da3690da544a0169f809481ef0819cbd4db78208c2dddd\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-AlZEx0GGOSlN8hdyAebWdqZ3Bk5RlzO9aC0Uc6s1Bunvmt5DhhDSRO3guFlFrSyi_lkfe_0kefFBtG1ftVhjEhCF-P8kvoNdyrABiHLy3zwy5VI3PultKiH8MFoVooLVQyOlwterlypfhtbHZ1jduXYDWb3-xhqpfP4haX36rNfU51QC8vkodCCIp8i64PAQxfC6ZamicI-fmENu-HJ_4SlJUajBKu3LEMgNzs-hSTZJxey_VylwQ_DE1LuYVDxDwv4M-mMIeGKaK19Z0goYxCJG5qrT2lFGYOm77-_q5ieTnX7bJ_7xdTRENbU6vh0IiIAgft8LOkjjkOnzhemcNkE9TWndBgjpeFJR1yL5J1cdOM1gAZmITIeNNQYUXVbSAjmQwb6-eyrWxrICam6MVg_flkf3mrgw2jqhez2GT42LMBUh4mRmvdi_t6Kr5QFlGpwhyrlpkDTRzSZMTwqVNeJrVz5UsNSLcEKhswSxBxu4JjNBmulBE-AZKdt5-iZyK7tfcf9qXdfWE1ZcNbBRTBlaswNZ_DOiRQzX1XrQp9BvyoIHNih5U2dKsN3HHJ_erHCC7QsDLm0zCUMNuvqOkpBMtdNTEgw914NslP0LjwlBlcBwPVfhAxNXkckZcBz7_ykBbdQSPfvzk7b7ygS38ycrbb6zrTHomin7dVKu5DyXzykQkVdGq3SYeXpZlhQX1Sz0Nbg59rurJ_MicLABi9mv5BfNJUvFSV7rCXA2Uk2_YaF51ZL76WoE-KmiKwRjAl__foFLzQVqoXhT28b25O_J3FHySdFVc0UcLIjwbVPky-tNwB6vzLgXnmN4-cDPJnMiWNajXfxUMDEwmTRTQpWL73c-ipfW-5Y_XfUpHj59KhGWzEbqYnNuwOiC-C3X0wxfGNc1yAaY0KluTnA-T-ol8DKjpFpFu5MXv3zdjQNy8dkTBlIzZW-3W2-QMHkL40mngkp2gQkfTdF9UEYaeayDwq1yTBuA9uujbvbaWPzdGyqOo8veV4cMFeGtbgLRgq-zaqr5duQYpTwNaWe46hGTx9kkIn_9eY8SIrdNlBqe8HXl1Z9B5l6zFMfMV4xQdu2ZJgY0LmCqwp9p4osiQIFuQ9QOMwrs3EGBND_WAWLhFHwdR2V1C_KCBfb9keK1d52HIsM9TjgLt_PIlyrFbH2DgRtymn4fwrzaYGSonLTu1JGmlr1-dH2mH-OUD1BLCOaJl_s_y2My6Cf0cxt6eotI-x4yNfnqB_IfuARIjHGHdDOVFrPMjFn7D